Date: 1995-04-28

Title: A Note on the Majorana Theory for $j=1/2$ and $j=1$ Particle States

Comments: REVTEX file. 8pp. No figures. Contribution at the XVIII Oaxtepec

Symp. on Nuclear Physics. January 4-7, 1995Journal-ref: Rev.Mex.Fis. 41 (1995) 159-167

The wave equations for self/anti-self conjugate Majorana-McLennan-Case$j=1/2$ and $j=1$ spinors, proposed by Ahluwalia, are re-written to covariantform. The connection with the Foldy-Nigam-Bargmann-Wightman-Wigner (FNBWW) typequantum field theory is discussed.